<br>
Just grab 8 of anything and load up Pillar of Lightning. (okay skip giants and wurms for now, but everything else that isn't SoW'd is fair game.)<br>
<br>
Snare the first 4, then the second. round up into a mob and Let'er Rip.<br>
<br>
Nice Plat drops, some lower end dropped gems, and vendor trash. <br>
<br>
Heck you might even still get some xp too. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/umyztic.showPublicProfile?language=EN>MyztiC</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer<BR>Born-Again Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 598<br> <font color=#ffffff>(9/17/02 10:17 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Cash zones</span><hr size=1> From 1 to 12sh in GFay and BB, also few of the quests (like hammer from Qeynos) sold for obsene amounts of plat at that time.<br>
From 12 to 20 in Cauldron (orcs) and Unrest.<br>
From 20 to 30 mostly in Cazic Thule and trips to Mistmoore and Unrest. (FS, Bronze sold well to vendors and as a wiz it was easy to make selling trips).<br>
From 30 to 50, best cash first came from LGuk (plat, FS and items), then from BB dorfs (12pp a pop) and last from Kedge (rare items and gems).<br>
From 50 to 60 there are tons of zones to make cash, but I usually concentrated on making exp. For example a good night in Skyfire nets about 2k (without player to player trading) and regular night nets around 800pp. It all depends if you're lucky with gem drops and spells that sell for 27pp a pop.<br>
<br>
BUT, the best way for me to make cash is to farm some items and put them for sale in bazaar. It usually requires a group to get said good items and it also requires luck on rolls... but that is still the best way to make cash for me. Since bazaar opened, I cleared twinks and banks from junk that I've accumulated in 3+ years and managed to net around 400k. The bazaar was gift from heavens. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=73401">Myztic Mythoclast</a><br> 
